author: Amanda Marrazzo
title: Woodstock police investigating 'less-than-natural' death
text:
Police are investigating the death of a man found in a home in far northwest suburban Woodstock on Sunday afternoon.
About 12:30 p.m. Woodstock police responded to a home in the 600 block of Leah Lane after receiving a request for a well-being check, according to a news release from the Woodstock Police Department. Police said the call came from an acquaintance of the man. Police found the man dead "under circumstances that are suspected to be less than natural."
Police said that this is an "isolated incident and that there is no immediate threat to the general public."
The investigation is being conducted by Woodstock police, the McHenry County Major Investigations Assistance Team, the coroner's office, the state's attorney's office and the United States Marshal's office.
Check back later for more details.
Amanda Marrazzo is a freelance reporter.
 Woodstock
